hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Flux conservation during the rapid TQ implies the total linked poloidal flux is unchanged:
$$\Psi_0 = (L_{ext}+L_{int,0})\,I_{p0}
\;=\;(L_{ext}+L_{int,f})\,I_{p,f}\,.$$
2. Solve for the post‐TQ total current $I_{p,f}$:
$$I_{p,f}
=\frac{L_{ext}+L_{int,0}}{L_{ext}+L_{int,f}}\;I_{p0}\,.$$
3. After the TQ the cold plasma splits into two parallel toroidal paths (core and halo) with resistances $R_c$ and $R_h$. The same toroidal voltage $V$ appears across each:
$$V=R_c\,I_c=R_h\,I_h,\quad I_c+I_h=I_{p,f}.$$
4. From $I_c+I_h=I_{p,f}$ and $I_h=\frac{V}{R_h}$, $I_c=\frac{V}{R_c}$:
$$\frac{V}{R_h}+\frac{V}{R_c}=I_{p,f}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
V=I_{p,f}\,\frac{R_c\,R_h}{R_c+R_h}\,.$$
5. Hence the halo current is
$$I_h=\frac{V}{R_h}
=I_{p,f}\,\frac{R_c}{R_c+R_h}
=\Bigl(\frac{L_{ext}+L_{int,0}}{L_{ext}+L_{int,f}}\Bigr)\,I_{p0}\,\frac{R_c}{R_c+R_h}\,.$$
6. The halo current fraction is
$$f_h=\frac{I_h}{I_{p0}}
=\frac{L_{ext}+L_{int,0}}{L_{ext}+L_{int,f}}\;\frac{R_c}{R_c+R_h}\,. $$
